\begin_layout Plain Layout
In
\bar under
tegrator cells have distinct axonal projection patterns.

\bar default
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

(A) Colored panels show three views of reconstructed cells with same axon
 projection patterns.
 Top left, 6 integrator cell with ipsilateral projecting axons - ipsi-only
 group, pink background.
 Top right, 2 integrator cells with ipsilaterally and putative contralateral
 projection – ipsi-contra, green background.
 Bottom left, 8 integrator cells with midline crossing contralateral only
 putative-axon – contra-only, orange background.
 Bottom right, 7, integrator cells with unknown axonal projection – unknown,
 blue background.
 On the neurites, red circles - postsynaptic sites, green circles - presynaptic
 sites.
 
